three spreadsheets: total students, male students, and female students. The Excel file contains data on allegations of harassment or bullying by type of allegations for all states.","distribution_titles":["Allegations of Harassment or Bullying","On Basis of Disability - Disciplined ","On Basis of Disability - Reported","On Basis of Race - Disciplined","On Basis of Race - Reported","On Basis of Sex - Disciplined","On Basis of Sex - Reported"],"harvest_record":"https://catalog.data.gov/harvest_record/c4d2afc2-0d60-4a75-9a68-46c6a3dec87f","harvest_record_raw":"https://catalog.data.gov/harvest_record/c4d2afc2-0d60-4a75-9a68-46c6a3dec87f/raw","has_spatial":false,"identifier":"a6312d29-ef5b-4df4-97ea-5da38ce36a7f","keyword":["Elementary-and-secondary","Language","civil-rights","minority","national","ocr","office-for-civil-rights-ocr","race","student-enrollment","student-retention","students"],"last_harvested_date":"2026-05-08T20:16:21.838712","organization":{"aliases":["dept"],"description":null,"id":"217e855b-cd64-4ebc-958b-abbbb0f57ac2","logo":"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/GSA/logo/refs/heads/master/ed.png","name":"Department of Education","organization_type":"Federal Government","slug":"ed"},"popularity":16148,"publisher":"Office for Civil Rights (OCR)","slug":"2015-16-harassment-or-bullying-by-basis-category-civil-rights-data-collection","spatial_centroid":null,"spatial_shape":null,"theme":[],"title":"2015-16 Harassment or Bullying by Basis Category Civil Rights Data Collection"},{"_score":1.0,"_sort":[1.0,14689,"f305cd9b-8994-4115-949f-49f50cdae347"],"dcat":{"@type":"dcat:Dataset","accessLevel":"public","bureauCode":["018:00"],"contactPoint":{"@type":"vcard:Contact","fn":"CRDC Team","hasEmail":"mailto:odp@ed.gov"},"description":"The Civil Rights Data Collection, 2017-18 (CRDC 2017-18) is part of the Civil Rights Data Collection (CRDC) program; program data are available beginning with the 2000 collection at https://civilrightsdata.ed.gov/data. CRDC 2017-18 is a cross-sectional survey that collects data on key education and civil rights issues in the nation's public schools, which include student enrollment and educational programs and services, disaggregated by race/ethnicity, sex, limited English proficiency, and disability. LEAs submit administrative records about schools in the district. CRDC 2017-18 is a universe survey. Key statistics produced from CRDC 2017-18 can provide information about critical civil rights issues as well as contextual information on the state of civil rights in the nation, including enrollment demographics, advanced placement, school discipline, and special education services.","distribution":[{"@type":"dcat:Distribution","description":"A public-use data file containing the entire CRDC year-of-choice data set in CSV format can be downloaded in a zip file.","downloadURL":"https://civilrightsdata.ed.gov/assets/ocr/docs/2017-18-crdc-data.zip","format":"ZIP","mediaType":"application/zip","title":"2017-18-crdc-data.zip"}],"identifier":"dd80845b-924e-40d3-964c-dd4875113f0a","keyword":["Elementary-and-secondary","Language","civil-rights","discrimination","enrollment-demographics","minority-groups","national","office-for-civil-rights-ocr","race","student-retention","students"],"landingPage":"https://civilrightsdata.ed.gov/data","license":"http://www.opendefinition.org/licenses/cc-by","modified":"2024-10-23T14:31:02.368789","programCode":["018:000"],"publisher":{"@type":"org:Organization","name":"Office for Civil Rights (OCR)"},"title":"Civil Rights Data Collection (CRDC) for the 2017-18 school year"},"description":"The Civil Rights Data Collection, 2017-18 (CRDC 2017-18) is part of the Civil Rights Data Collection (CRDC) program; program data are available beginning with the 2000 collection at https://civilrightsdata.ed.gov/data. CRDC 2017-18 is a cross-sectional survey that collects data on key education and civil rights issues in the nation's public schools, which include student enrollment and educational programs and services, disaggregated by race/ethnicity, sex, limited English proficiency, and disability. LEAs submit administrative records about schools in the district. CRDC 2017-18 is a universe survey. Key statistics produced from CRDC 2017-18 can provide information about critical civil rights issues as well as contextual information on the state of civil rights in the nation, including enrollment demographics, advanced placement, school discipline, and special education services.","distribution_titles":["2017-18-crdc-data.zip"],"harvest_record":"https://catalog.data.gov/harvest_record/98a6ce25-0fc9-4954-af90-b7a5bb742e40","harvest_record_raw":"https://catalog.data.gov/harvest_record/98a6ce25-0fc9-4954-af90-b7a5bb742e40/raw","has_spatial":false,"identifier":"dd80845b-924e-40d3-964c-dd4875113f0a","keyword":["Elementary-and-secondary","Language","civil-rights","discrimination","enrollment-demographics","minority-groups","national","office-for-civil-rights-ocr","race","student-retention","students"],"last_harvested_date":"2026-05-08T20:16:25.118161","organization":{"aliases":["dept"],"description":null,"id":"217e855b-cd64-4ebc-958b-abbbb0f57ac2","logo":"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/GSA/logo/refs/heads/master/ed.png","name":"Department of Education","organization_type":"Federal Government","slug":"ed"},"popularity":14689,"publisher":"Office for Civil Rights (OCR)","slug":"civil-rights-data-collection-crdc-for-the-2017-18-school-year","spatial_centroid":null,"spatial_shape":null,"theme":[],"title":"Civil Rights Data Collection (CRDC) for the 2017-18 school year"},{"_score":1.0,"_sort":[1.0,14411,"eef7a1f5-f646-4c70-8600-b9f6e3c2a60d"],"dcat":{"@type":"dcat:Dataset","accessLevel":"public","bureauCode":["018:00"],"contactPoint":{"@type":"vcard:Contact","fn":"CRDC Team","hasEmail":"mailto:odp@ed.gov"},"description":"This set of Excel files contains data on students reported as harassed or bullied or disciplined for harassment or bullying on the basis of sex