age","civil-rights","minority","national","ocr","office-for-civil-rights-ocr","race","state","student-enrollment","student-retention","students"],"landingPage":"https://civilrightsdata.ed.gov/estimations/2013-2014","license":"http://www.opendefinition.org/licenses/cc-by","modified":"2024-10-23T14:48:52.027638","programCode":["018:000"],"publisher":{"@type":"org:Organization","name":"Office for Civil Rights (OCR)"},"title":"2013-14 Mathematics and Science Civil Rights Data Collection"},"description":"The 2013-14 tables are based on data collected from all of the nation\u2019s school districts and schools\u2014approximately 16,500 school districts and 96,500 schools. This Excel file contains data for schools offering classes in mathematics and science, and student enrollment for all states. The file contains one spreadsheet for total schools. For all mathematics and science courses, there are three spreadsheets: total students, male students, and female students.","distribution_titles":["Schools Offering Mathematics and Science Classes","Advanced Mathematics","Algebra I Grade 11-12","Algebra I Grade 7-8","Algebra I Grade 9-10","Algebra II","Biology ","Calculus","Chemistry","Geometry ","Physics"],"harvest_record":"https://catalog.data.gov/harvest_record/6268d2e0-586a-48e7-80e1-208ff07a2136","harvest_record_raw":"https://catalog.data.gov/harvest_record/6268d2e0-586a-48e7-80e1-208ff07a2136/raw","has_spatial":false,"identifier":"a0ba036f-c364-415b-8516-32491541a488","keyword":["Elementary-and-secondary","Language","civil-rights","minority","national","ocr","office-for-civil-rights-ocr","race","state","student-enrollment","student-retention","students"],"last_harvested_date":"2026-05-12T20:55:59.087366","organization":{"aliases":["dept"],"description":null,"id":"217e855b-cd64-4ebc-958b-abbbb0f57ac2","logo":"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/GSA/logo/refs/heads/master/ed.png","name":"Department of Education","organization_type":"Federal Government","slug":"ed"},"popularity"